HEADWORD: Windgall
<hw>Wind"gall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A
soft tumor or synovial swelling on the fetlock joint of a horse; -- so
called from having formerly been supposed to contain air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

